title: 113: STEAK (Rachael Finley): I Didn’t Know What Was In the World, But I Wanted To Go See It
itunes:title: 113: STEAK (Rachael Finley): I Didn’t Know What Was In the World, But I Wanted To Go See It
description:
This week Jeremy interviews fashion designer and author Steak (Rachael Finley)

On this episode Steak and Jeremy talk Master P Skateparks, growing up in South Florida, taking an early interest in fashion, the frivolous nature of gifting, how she landed her first tour selling merch, Psyopus, landing an internship at Hydra Head Records in Los Angeles, being diagnosed with cancer, becoming a fit model, starting her bad advice Tumblr, finding out she was in remission the first time, the way her first brand Teenage started which lead to Hot Lava, being on Viceland and moving to MTV, co-hosting Wonderland with Lizzo and Myke Wright, moving back to fashion, the release of her memoir “Nobody Ever Told Me Anything” and so much more!

SUBSCRIBE TO THE PATREON to hear a bonus episode where Steak answered questions that were submitted by subscribers!

Follow the show on INSTAGRAM and TWITTER
